    "summary": "Recognize predicates of the form `((X + C) & ~M) == 0` or equivalent `!=` forms, when `X` is constrained by `!range` so that the accepted values are exactly those in-range values with all bits in some mask set. Canonicalize to a direct bit-test such as `((X & AndMask) == AndMask)` or, for a single-bit mask, `(X & Bit) != 0`.",
    "motivation_from_example": {
      "source_form": "For `X : i8 range(0,4)`, `((X - 1) & -3) == 0` accepts exactly `{1,3}`.",
      "canonical_form": "Within `range(0,4)`, `{1,3}` are exactly the in-range values with bit 0 set, so this is equivalent to `(X & 1) != 0`."
    },
    "generalization": {
      "accepted_set_view": "The transformation applies when the predicate denotes a finite set of values that, under the operand's known bits/range, is exactly the set of values where every bit in some nonzero `AndMask` is set.",
      "canonical_predicate": "If the matching set is exact, rewrite to `icmp eq (and X, AndMask), AndMask`; if `AndMask` is a single bit, this may be further canonicalized to `icmp ne (and X, AndMask), 0`.",
      "preconditions": [
        "The input has sufficient `!range`/known-bits information to bound all values being considered.",
        "The accepted values form a power-of-two-sized set compatible with varying only the range-permitted free bits not covered by `AndMask`.",
        "All accepted constants share the bits in `AndMask` (`AndMask` is their bitwise AND), and no out-of-range values satisfying the bit-test are possible."
      ],
      "instcombine_fold_shape": [
        "Either match the arithmetic/bitmask predicate directly, or enumerate the implied accepted constants under known range.",
        "Compute a candidate `AndMask` as the AND of all accepted constants.",
        "Use known bits/range to verify exactness: bits required by `AndMask` are feasible, and the number of unconstrained varying bits equals `log2(case_count)`.",
        "Replace with `(X & AndMask) == AndMask` / `(X & Bit) != 0`."
      ],
      "equivalent_source_forms": [
        "`((X - K) & C) == 0`",
        "`icmp ne ((X - K) & C), 0` with inverted true/false sense",
        "same predicate with `or disjoint`-equivalent constants such as `-2`, `-3`, `-5`, `-9`, etc. depending on mask",
        "width-generalized forms over i4/i8/i16/i32/i64 where range metadata makes the exact accepted set provable"
